{"timestamp":"2026-06-05T09:52:58.212Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"call_YRvoSI2h8Ri3osrm8VYzkiqi","output":"Chunk ID: 41dbc4\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1590\nOutput:\n   260\t    await waitForRegistrationStatus(page);\n   261\t    await testInfo.attach('markdown', {\n   262\t      body: `\n   263\t  After you have selected your event, you can see the event description and your options for registration.\n   264\t  _Note:_ If you are not logged it, please follow the instructions to do so.\n   265\t\n   266\t  ### Free events\n   267\t  Here we will make a distinction for free events and paid events (covered further down).\n   268\t  Participant options are labeled separately from organizer/helper options, which use **Sign up as organizer/helper** copy when you are helping run the event.\n   269\t  When a participant option is full, registration changes to a distinct **Join waitlist** action instead of pretending a normal spot is still available. Waitlisted participants can return to the event page and use **Leave waitlist** before the event starts.\n   270\t  If you open a direct event link but your account does not match the roles required by any available option, the event remains visible and the registration area explains that registration is unavailable for your account.`,\n   271\t    });\n   272\t    await takeScreenshot(\n   273\t      testInfo,\n   274\t      page.getByRole('heading', { level: 2, name: 'Registration' }),\n   275\t      page,\n   276\t      'Free event registration options with participant and organizer choices',\n   277\t    );\n   278\t    await testInfo.attach('markdown', {\n   279\t      body: `\n   280\t  Free registration cards can also offer registration-time add-ons and required questions. Choose the quantity you want, answer any required questions, and then register. After registration, selected add-ons are shown with the active registration so participants can review what they picked. Question answers are stored with the registration for organizers.`,\n   281\t    });\n   282\t    const participantRegistrationCard = page\n   283\t      .locator('app-event-registration-option')\n   284\t      .filter({ hasText: 'Participant registration' })\n   285\t      .first();\n   286\t    await expect(participantRegistrationCard).toBeVisible({ timeout: 20_000 });\n   287\t    await expect(\n   288\t      participantRegistrationCard.getByText('Snack voucher'),\n   289\t    ).toBeVisible();\n   290\t    await expect(\n   291\t      participantRegistrationCard.getByLabel(registrationQuestion.title),\n   292\t    ).toBeVisible();\n   293\t    await expect(\n   294\t      participantRegistrationCard.getByRole('button', { name: 'Register' }),\n   295\t    ).toBeDisabled();\n   296\t    await participantRegistrationCard.getByLabel('Quantity').fill('2');\n   297\t    await participantRegistrationCard\n   298\t      .getByLabel(registrationQuestion.title)\n   299\t      .fill('Vegetarian snack, please.');\n   300\t    await participantRegistrationCard\n   301\t      .getByRole('button', { name: 'Register' })\n   302\t      .click();\n   303\t    await expect(page.getByText('You are registered')).toBeVisible();\n   304\t    await expect(page.getByText('2 x Snack voucher')).toBeVisible();\n   305\t\n   306\t    const registration = await database.query.eventRegistrations.findFirst({\n   307\t      where: {\n   308\t        eventId: freeEventId,\n   309\t        registrationOptionId: freeOptionId,\n   310\t        status: 'CONFIRMED',\n   930\t\n   931\t      await expect(\n   932\t        page.getByRole('heading', { name: 'Registration unavailable' }),\n   933\t      ).toBeVisible();\n   934\t      await expect(\n   935\t        page.getByText(\n   936\t          'This event is visible from the direct link, but your account is not eligible for the available registration options.',\n   937\t        ),\n   938\t      ).toBeVisible();\n   939\t      await expect(\n   940\t        page.getByRole('button', { name: /^Register$/ }),\n   941\t      ).toHaveCount(0);\n   942\t      await takeScreenshot(\n   943\t        testInfo,\n   944\t        page.getByRole('heading', { name: 'Registration unavailable' }),\n   945\t        page,\n   946\t        'Role-ineligible registration state',\n   947\t      );\n   948\t\n   949\t      await testInfo.attach('markdown', {\n   950\t        body: `\n  1050\t    await gotoEventDetail(page, paidEvent.id);\n  1051\t    await waitForRegistrationStatus(page);\n  1052\t    const payButton = page.getByRole('button', { name: /Pay/i }).first();\n  1053\t    await takeScreenshot(\n  1054\t      testInfo,\n  1055\t      registrationOptionCard(page, 'Pay'),\n  1056\t      page,\n  1057\t      'Paid event registration options before starting Stripe Checkout',\n  1058\t    );\n  1059\t    await testInfo.attach('markdown', {\n  1060\t      body: `\n  1061\t  By clicking the **Pay and register** button, you are starting the payment process.\n  1062\t  Paid guest spots are included in the Stripe Checkout quantity and reserve the matching capacity while payment is pending.\n  1063\t  Afterwards, you can either finish the registration by paying or cancel your payment and registration in case you changed your mind. Cancelling a pending payment registration releases every selected buyer and guest spot and expires the pending checkout when possible.`,\n  1064\t    });\n  1065\t    await takeScreenshot(\n  1066\t      testInfo,\n  1067\t      payButton,\n  1068\t      page,\n  1069\t      'Paid registration button before the pending checkout recovery state',\n  1070\t    );\n  1071\t    const findCheckoutTransaction = async () => {\n  1072\t      if (checkoutTransactionId) {\n  1073\t        return database.query.transactions.findFirst({\n  1074\t          where: {\n  1075\t            id: checkoutTransactionId,\n  1228\t    await registrationStatus.waitFor({ state: 'detached', timeout: 20_000 });\n  1229\t    const registeredMessage = page.getByText('You are registered');\n  1230\t    await expect(registeredMessage).toBeVisible({ timeout: 20_000 });\n  1231\t    await testInfo.attach('markdown', {\n  1232\t      body: `\n  1233\t  ### Successful paid registration\n  1234\t  After successful payment, you are redirected back to the event page and shown your registration confirmation.\n  1235\t  Your ticket details and QR code are now available.`,\n  1236\t    });\n  1237\t    await takeScreenshot(\n  1238\t      testInfo,\n  1239\t      page.getByRole('heading', { level: 2, name: 'Registration' }),\n  1240\t      page,\n  1241\t      'Event details after successful paid registration',\n  1242\t    );\n  1243\t    await database\n  1244\t      .delete(schema.transactions)\n  1245\t      .where(\n  1246\t        and(\n"}}
