{"timestamp":"2026-06-05T10:11:15.725Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"agent_message","message":"Pushed another focused stabilization slice to PR #62.\n\nCommit: `a459eb6f0` `Focus global admin docs screenshots`\n\nWhat changed:\n- `tests/docs/admin/global-admin.doc.ts` now highlights concrete tenant summary, empty search, relaunch scope, detail review, and edit form surfaces instead of heading-only targets.\n- `helpers/testing/generated-documentation-source.spec.ts` now guards those concrete targets.\n- Updated `STABILIZATION.md` and `tests/test-inventory.md` to document the stronger global-admin docs evidence.\n\nVerification passed:\n- `bun run format:write`\n- `bun run lint`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `bun run test:unit:server -- helpers/testing/generated-documentation-source.spec.ts helpers/testing/stabilization-source.spec.ts`\n- `bun run test:e2e:docs -- --list tests/docs/admin/global-admin.doc.ts`\n- WebStorm errors-only diagnostics on edited TS files\n\nI also tried the focused global-admin docs run itself. It did not reach the changed doc on `4577` because Auth0 rejected the generated callback URL; retrying with `APP_HOST_PORT=4200` failed before Playwright because port `4200` is already allocated locally. I stopped the generated Compose project afterward and restored `.env.dev` back to `BASE_URL=http://localhost:4577`.\n\nPR #62 is now at head `a459eb6f0`; active-head checks have restarted and are queued/pending: E2E, CodeQL, Copilot setup, Git Town, and CodeRabbit.\n\n::git-stage{cwd=\"/Users/hedde/.codex/worktrees/e159/evorto\"}\n::git-commit{cwd=\"/Users/hedde/.codex/worktrees/e159/evorto\"}\n::git-push{cwd=\"/Users/hedde/.codex/worktrees/e159/evorto\" branch=\"codex/stabilization-flow-coverage\"}","phase":"final_answer","memory_citation":null}}
