{"timestamp":"2026-06-05T10:19:00.558Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"agent_message","message":"Pushed commit `909667d7` (`Focus event management docs screenshots`) to PR #62.\n\nWhat changed:\n- `tests/docs/events/event-management.doc.ts` now targets concrete UI surfaces for docs screenshots: event list, template choice card, event detail header, registration option, and role-picker form.\n- `helpers/testing/generated-documentation-source.spec.ts` now guards those concrete targets and rejects the old heading-only screenshot anchors.\n- Updated `STABILIZATION.md` and `tests/test-inventory.md`.\n\nVerified:\n- `bun run format:write`\n- `bun run lint`\n- `bun run test:unit:server -- helpers/testing/generated-documentation-source.spec.ts helpers/testing/stabilization-source.spec.ts`\n- `bun run test:e2e:docs -- --list tests/docs/events/event-management.doc.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- WebStorm errors-only diagnostics on edited TypeScript files\n\nCI status at head `909667d7`:\n- CodeQL: green\n- Git Town: green\n- CodeRabbit: green\n- Copilot setup: green\n- E2E Baseline: still running, currently in `Warm CI dependency caches`\n\nI also checked the Neon cleanup and Font Awesome concerns:\n- Local Neon cleanup dry-run reports only `main`: `total=1, protected=1, active_test=0, stale_deleted=0, ttl=2h`.\n- CI already has the Font Awesome mitigation in place: public registry override, Bun package cache, node_modules cache, Docker Bun cache mount, serial cache warmer, and `offline-required` installs in non-warmer jobs so parallel jobs fail instead of re-downloading Font Awesome packages.\n\n::git-stage{cwd=\"/Users/hedde/.codex/worktrees/e159/evorto\"}\n::git-commit{cwd=\"/Users/hedde/.codex/worktrees/e159/evorto\"}\n::git-push{cwd=\"/Users/hedde/.codex/worktrees/e159/evorto\" branch=\"codex/stabilization-flow-coverage\"}","phase":"final_answer","memory_citation":null}}
{"timestamp":"2026-06-05T10:19:00.561Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"output_text","text":"Pushed commit `909667d7` (`Focus event management docs screenshots`) to PR #62.\n\nWhat changed:\n- `tests/docs/events/event-management.doc.ts` now targets concrete UI surfaces for docs screenshots: event list, template choice card, event detail header, registration option, and role-picker form.\n- `helpers/testing/generated-documentation-source.spec.ts` now guards those concrete targets and rejects the old heading-only screenshot anchors.\n- Updated `STABILIZATION.md` and `tests/test-inventory.md`.\n\nVerified:\n- `bun run format:write`\n- `bun run lint`\n- `bun run test:unit:server -- helpers/testing/generated-documentation-source.spec.ts helpers/testing/stabilization-source.spec.ts`\n- `bun run test:e2e:docs -- --list tests/docs/events/event-management.doc.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- WebStorm errors-only diagnostics on edited TypeScript files\n\nCI status at head `909667d7`:\n- CodeQL: green\n- Git Town: green\n- CodeRabbit: green\n- Copilot setup: green\n- E2E Baseline: still running, currently in `Warm CI dependency caches`\n\nI also checked the Neon cleanup and Font Awesome concerns:\n- Local Neon cleanup dry-run reports only `main`: `total=1, protected=1, active_test=0, stale_deleted=0, ttl=2h`.\n- CI already has the Font Awesome mitigation in place: public registry override, Bun package cache, node_modules cache, Docker Bun cache mount, serial cache warmer, and `offline-required` installs in non-warmer jobs so parallel jobs fail instead of re-downloading Font Awesome packages.\n\n::git-stage{cwd=\"/Users/hedde/.codex/worktrees/e159/evorto\"}\n::git-commit{cwd=\"/Users/hedde/.codex/worktrees/e159/evorto\"}\n::git-push{cwd=\"/Users/hedde/.codex/worktrees/e159/evorto\" branch=\"codex/stabilization-flow-coverage\"}"}],"phase":"final_answer"}}
